subSubSection.paragraph:
Galumna (Neogalumna) specifica
sp. n. is morphologically most similar to 
Galumna (Neogalumna) tolstikovi
Ermilov & Anichkin, 2014 from Vietnam (see 
Ermilov and Anichkin 2014b
) in having straight lamellar lines, short prodorsal setae, setiform bothridial setae, setal alveoli cx and striate genital plates. However, the new species differs from the latter by larger body size (498-531 
x
348-365 vs. 381-415 
x
265-298 in 
Galumna (Neogalumna) tolstikovi
), well developed and barbed interlamellar setae (vs. minute in 
Galumna (Neogalumna) tolstikovi
), longest rostral setae on the prodorsum (vs. rostral and lamellar similar in length in 
Galumna (Neogalumna) tolstikovi
), a striate basal part of prodorsum (vs. not striate in in 
Galumna (Neogalumna) tolstikovi
), an elongated postanal porose area (vs. oval in 
Galumna (Neogalumna) tolstikovi
) and the absence of setal alveoli la (vs. present in 
Galumna (Neogalumna) tolstikovi
).
